BWIM will be hosting its annual celebration recognizing Black women in music! The event will take place on Friday, February 3rd, from 11 am until 6 pm, in Los Angeles. We will be recognizing Black women within the music industry-- including artists, executives, and of course Grammy nominees (past and present)💐💜

Past Honorees include: Yolanda Adams, Kelly Price, Tasha Cobbs, YOLA, Spice, and more!

For media passes and partnership opportunities, click link in our bio! 

Space is limited. Tickets are first come first serve!

#blackwomeninmedia #grammys #grammys2023 #party #celebration

This journey is joyous, enlightening, painful, and exciting. It’s a journey of growth and transformation. To discover myself is the most rewarding part of this experience and I’m looking forward to more of it. #Thankful

social_posts.post_text: Thank you to #BlackLegacyPartners for recognizing me during their Black History Month celebration. A pleasure meeting Emmy award-winning #BlackWomeninMedia  @themaponton who did a wonderful job at being our Mistress of Ceremonies. Congratulations to all of my fellow honorees.

Yesterday, I terrorized my son in helping me to create videos to reach partners. I’m not usually in front of the lens, and as uncomfortable as I was, I’m confident that these videos will help reach my community in a deeper and more efficient way. There are some exciting things in the works! 

Stay tuned to seeing more of me #HonoringmyWork
No matter what.

Yesterday evening I had the esteemed honor of joining the amazing #Yola for the #NAACPImageAwards dinner. The Black excellence that was in the room left me in awe.
